        <num>CC 2622</num>
        <heading>2622.  Warranty of assignor</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 2622.  Warranty of assignor
The assignor of an option to buy a thing warrants the existence of that option, but does not warrant that the person who granted it can be required to make a final sale.
If, upon exercise of the option, the person who granted it fails to make a final sale, the assignee has against the assignor the same rights as a buyer without warranty has against the seller.</p>
        </content>
